Binary Search Tree Implementation in C
This repository contains a simple implementation of a Binary Search Tree (BST) in C. It demonstrates fundamental operations on BSTs including insertion, deletion, and traversal.
ğŸš€ Features
- Insertion: Add new nodes into the BST while maintaining order.
- Deletion: Remove nodes with proper handling of three cases:
- Node with no children
- Node with one child
- Node with two children (using inorder successor)
- Traversal Methods:
- Preorder (Root â†’ Left â†’ Right)
- Inorder (Left â†’ Root â†’ Right)
- Postorder (Left â†’ Right â†’ Root)
- Menu-driven program: Interactive console interface for performing operations.
